## path to poly-G raw data directory (marker length files)

  ## load marker lengths and get the average length of each marker in each sample
  get_markers <- function(marker_dir) {

  marker <- suppressMessages(read_tsv(marker_dir))
  
  # getting the marker name
  int_file <- tail(str_split(marker_dir, "/")[[1]], 1) 
  marker_name <- head(str_split(int_file, "_")[[1]], 1)

  cols <- NCOL(marker) +1 

  marker  %>% 
    rowid_to_column("length")  %>% 
    pivot_longer(cols=c(2:cols), names_to="sample", values_to="Frequency")  %>% 
    group_by(sample)  %>% 
    mutate(Frequency=Frequency/sum(Frequency),
            sample=str_remove(sample, "_[1-3]$")) %>%
    mutate(polyG=marker_name) 
    
  }

In [12]:
genome_lengths <- cn_ranges %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    filter(sample %in% final_samples, !(seqnames %in% c("chrMT", "chrX"))) %>%
    group_by(seqnames) %>%
    slice_max(end, with_ties=F) %>%
    mutate(
        seqnames = as.character(seqnames), seqnames = str_remove(seqnames, "chr"),
        seqnames = as.numeric(seqnames) + 1, seqnames=paste0("chr", seqnames)
    ) %>% 
    ungroup() %>% 
    mutate(end_x =cumsum(as.numeric(end))) %>% 
    select(seqnames, end_x) %>% 
    mutate(seqnames=ifelse(seqnames=="chr23", "chrX", seqnames))

In [18]:
round2 = function(x, digits) {
  posneg = sign(x)
  z = abs(x)*10^digits
  z = z + 0.5 + sqrt(.Machine$double.eps)
  z = trunc(z)
  z = z/10^digits
  z*posneg
}

e4_meanlengths <- markes_cna %>%
    group_by(sample, polyG, segTCN) %>%
    mutate(Frequency = Frequency / sum(Frequency)) %>%
    summarize(length = sum(length * Frequency)) %>%
    dplyr::rename(marker = polyG) %>%
    filter(sample %in% final_samples) %>%
    ungroup() %>% 
    add_count(marker) %>% 
    filter(n==max(n))

Adding purity correction¶

In [39]:
meanlengths_corrected <- markes_cna_purity %>% 
    filter(sample %in% final_samples) %>% 
    group_by(sample, polyG, segTCN, purity) %>%
    summarize(length = sum(Frequency * length)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    drop_na() %>% 
    add_count(polyG) %>% 
    filter(n==max(n)) %>% 
    mutate(segTCN=round(segTCN), purity=purity) %>% 
    group_by(polyG) %>% 
    mutate(
      length =
        (length * (segTCN * purity + 2 * (1 - purity)) - (length[sample == "Normal1"] * 2 * (1 - purity)))
        / (segTCN * purity)
    ) %>%       
    mutate(length = length - length[sample == "Normal1"], 
    # assigning all Nax43 samples the mean length of Nax43 samples with copy number of 2
    length = ifelse(polyG == "Nax43" & sample!="Normal1", mean(length[segTCN == 2 & sample!="Normal1"]), length)) %>%
    dplyr::rename(marker = polyG) %>%
        ungroup()

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'sample', 'polyG', 'segTCN'. You can
override using the `.groups` argument.

plot_e4_tree <- function(tree) {
  subject_ggtree <- ggtree(tree, size = 1.5) +
    theme_tree2() +
    theme(
      axis.line.x = element_line(linewidth = 1.5),
      axis.title.x = element_text(size = 35, color = "black"),
      axis.text.x = element_text(size = 35, color = "black"),
      axis.ticks.x = element_line(color = "black", linewidth = 1),
      axis.ticks.length.x = unit(0.2, "cm"), plot.title = element_text(size = 35)
    )

  # maximum y dimension for plotting
  max.y <- max(subject_ggtree$data$y) + 1

  # maximum x dimension for plotting
  max.x <- max(subject_ggtree$data$x) * 1.1

  # annotating the sample type
  subject_ggtree$data <- subject_ggtree$data %>%
    mutate(
      type = str_extract(label, "(?<=E[0-9]{1,3})[:alpha:]{1,3}"),
      label = str_remove(label, "E4")
    )

  final_tree <- subject_ggtree +
    geom_tiplab(aes(color = type), size = 12) +
    coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, max.x)) +
    scale_color_manual(
      values = c(A = "purple2", L = "darkgreen", TD = "darkgreen", Per = "orange2", Liv = "orange2", Nor = "grey23", PT = "firebrick2"),
      guide = "none"
    )

  # finding the mrca of all tumor samples
  all_mrca <- getMRCA(tree, c(str_subset(tree$tip.label, "N|Ad", negate = TRUE)))
  print(subject_ggtree$data[subject_ggtree$data$node == all_mrca & subject_ggtree$data$isTip == F, ]$x)

  return(final_tree)
}

# function to scramble the tree labels for a permutation test
permute_quartet <- function(test_tree, constant_tree) {
    test_tree$tip.label <- sample(test_tree$tip.label[1:length(test_tree$tip.label)])
    status <- QuartetStatus(test_tree, cf = constant_tree)
    QuartetDivergence(status)
}
